# Tabby testing

**Every behavior change needs tests.** Fixes we ship must stay fixed, especially privacy, mood scoring, visit dedup, and classification.

## What to test

| Area | Location | Examples |
|------|----------|----------|
| Pure logic | `tests/*.test.ts` | classifier, visit dedup, dwell time, cat vitals |
| Orchestration | mock `utils/db` like `orchestrator.test.ts` | page visit scoring, dedup |
| Prompts/parsing | unit tests | `classify-prompt`, speech quality |
| Privacy rules | unit tests | no page-text paths, trackable URL filters |

Add tests **in the same task** as the feature, not later. When fixing a bug, add a test that fails without the fix.

## Conventions

- **Vitest**: `make test` / `make test-watch`
- Prefer **exported pure functions** over full extension E2E.
- Name tests by behavior: `skips duplicate visits to the same page`, `requires at least one minute in production`.
- Keep test files focused. Mirror small `utils/` modules.

## End of task

1. **`make check`** must pass.
2. Note the behavior in **`CHANGELOG.md`** under **`## X.Y.Z (unreleased)`**: one short line for end users (`tabby-workflow.mdc`).
3. New code without tests is incomplete unless docs-only or cosmetic CSS with no logic.
